14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:
13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>With ankle fractures,
the prognosis is good.&nbsp;It is possible to restore the normal functionality
of the leg in 90-95% of cases, provided that you go to the hospital as soon as
possible and fulfill all the appointments for treatment and rehabilitation.</span></p>

